  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "body": "*Description*:\r\nAs part of draining phase (`Envoy::Server::Instance::drainListeners`) Envoy instructs all workers to stop accepting new connections, however it does not close listening sockets.\r\n\r\nThis has few consequences:\r\n1. Clients observe it as hung socket and they have to timeout connection attempts instead of receiving fast-failure.\r\n2. If socket uses `SO_REUSEPORT` and some other Envoy instance is bound to the same port - only half of clients are able to establish successful connections, others are hung on draining Envoy.\r\n\r\nIs it acceptable to alter `ListenerManagerImpl::stopListeners` behavior to cleanup `active_listeners_` as soon as workers reported that they've stopped accepting new connections?\r\n\r\n\r\n*Relevant Links*:\r\n* https://github.com/envoyproxy/envoy/blob/dbb11fd6743e8dbc69c2cd3ff63251e898ccafc0/source/server/listener_manager_impl.cc#L793-L797\r\n",
